<chapter xml:id="ch-SE" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Sequences and Series (SE)</title>

  <objectives>
    <introduction>
      <p>
        This module describes sequences and how to add up sequences (called series):
      </p>
    </introduction>
      <dl>
        <li>
          <title>SE1</title>
          <p>
            I can work with sequences by determining its general form, computing its limit, and determining its convergence or divergence
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <title>SE2</title>
          <p>
            I can determine if a series is geometric, telescoping, or neither, and find its sum if possible.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <title>SE3</title>
          <p>
            I can use the integral test to determine if a series converges or diverges
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <title>SE4</title>
          <p>
            I can use the direct comparison test and limit comparison test to determine if a series converges or diverges
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <title>SE5</title>
          <p>
            I can determine the convergence or divergence of an alternating series, and determine if the series converges absolutely or conditionally.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <title>SE6</title>
          <p>
            I can use the ratio test and the root test to determine if a series converges absolutely, conditionally, or diverges
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <title>SE7</title>
          <p>
            I can determine if a series converges or diverges, and use the appropriate test to show why.  
          </p>
        </li>
      </dl>
  </objectives>
  
